  "summary": "After leaving the hall of the Inoue mansion, Xuyan (Yuzu) asks the narrator, Mr. Kouyama, who \"Brutus\" is, a question the narrator finds unsettling. As they walk toward a lake, Yuzu questions the narrator's strange behavior in the hall and shares an allegory about Val Selan, a carpenter who was poisoned by his wife and lived in a state of delusion before being perceived as a saint. She uses this story to discuss the nature of existence and subjective truth. When Wakamizu approaches, Yuzu leaves abruptly, leaving the narrator to wonder if her comments were directed at Selene or Shizuma.\n\nThe narrator then speaks with Mutsuzaki (Mukai), who remarks on Yuzu's cleverness. Mutsuzaki jokingly suggests there is a high probability that a woman is the murderer, though he quickly dismisses the comment to ease the narrator's unease.\n\nAs the narrator and Mutsuzaki return to the entrance gate, a piercing scream and the sound of Mahler's music signal a new tragedy. Inside, a dark brown box carved with scenes from the Kalevala—once cherished by Aku-ōn—is found stained with blood. In a macabre display reminiscent of Salome dancing with the severed head of John, Aku-ōn’s own severed head has been placed upon his prized box. Tsubaki and Kumiko observe the head of Akibas, noting that this new murder involves decapitation and introduces new elements to the ongoing mystery.",
